    "top_event": "Struck by Released Thermowell Plug",
    "incident_type": "Injury - Lost Time Accident (>3 days)",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Platform emergency shutdown activated by injured party",
      "A-Operator contacted Lead Operator via gaitronics",
      "Injured party moved to living quarters with assistance of three operators",
      "Medivac flight requested and executed after weather delay",
      "Injured party transported to hospital and underwent surgery"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 28, 2022, at approximately 0830 hours, a D-Operator employed by Wood PLC was performing a general overview inspection of W&T Offshore's Ship Shoal Block 300 Platform B. The operator noticed a leak from a \u00be inch thermowell plug on a pipeline pump discharge line and attempted to tighten it. The plug released unexpectedly and struck the operator in the lower abdomen, causing significant injury requiring surgery. The operator had approximately 8 months of offshore experience. Investigation determined the incident was caused by operator error and lack of job safety analysis for routine operations.",
    "recommendations": [],
